Spicy BBQ Coleslaw
  --Cook's Country

1 head green cabbage (2 1/2 lbs) quartered, cored, and shredded
2 tbsp sugar
salt and pepper
1 c mayo
1/3 c distilled white vinegar
1 tbsp prepared horseradish
1 tsp worcestershire sauce
1 garlic clove, minced
1/2 tsp dry mustard
1/4 tso cayenne pepper
2 carrots, peeled and shredded

Toss the cabbage, sugar, and 1/2 tsp salt together in bowl. Microwave, covered, until just beginning to wilt, ~3 min. Let cool slightly, ~5 min. Transfer half of cabbage to center of clean dish towel. Gather ends of towel to form bundle and twist to squeeze out excess water. Transfer to clean bowl and repeat with remaining cabbage. Whisk mayonnaise, vinegar, horseradish, worcestershire, garlic, mustard, cayenne, 1 1/4 tsp salt, and 1 tsp pepper in large bowl until smooth. Stir in cabbage and carrots and refrigerate, covered, until chilled, at least 1 hr. Serve. Can be refrigerated up to 2 days.


Notes: For extra kick, use 2 tbsp horseradish.
